## 🏷️ Branch Naming Convention

```
feature/<week>-<task_number>-<short-description>
```

| Prefix | When to use |
|---|---|
| `feature/` | New feature work |
| `fix/` | Bug fixes |
| `hotfix/` | Critical production fixes (merge directly to `main`) |
| `chore/` | Non-feature work (docs, CI, config) |

**Examples**:
- `feature/w1-1.3-master-erd`
- `feature/w1-1.4-jwt-auth-backend`
- `feature/w1-1.9-auth-guard-frontend`

---

## 🤝 Collaboration Rules

1. **Always branch from `main`** (after pulling latest).
2. **One feature = one branch = one PR**. No mixing tasks.
3. **PR titles follow**: `[W<week>-<task>] <Description>` (e.g., `[W1-1.4] JWT Authentication Backend`).
4. **Cross-review**: You review her frontend PRs, she reviews your backend PRs.
5. **No direct pushes to `main`** — everything via Pull Request.
6. **Rebase before PR**: `git pull --rebase origin main` to keep history clean.
7. **Resolve conflicts locally** before pushing.

### Merge Strategy

```
main (protected)
 ├── feature/w1-1.3-master-erd          ← You (Backend)
 ├── feature/w1-1.4-jwt-auth-backend    ← You (Backend)
 ├── feature/w1-1.8-react-project-init  ← Collaborator (Frontend)
 ├── feature/w1-1.9-auth-guard-frontend ← Collaborator (Frontend)
 └── ...
```

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Dependency Order Matters!** Some frontend features depend on backend APIs being merged first. The priority order below reflects this — backend features are listed before their frontend counterparts when a dependency exists.

