## 🚀 Immediate Action Plan — Authentication Sprint

Since we're starting with **Authentication** (Epic 1), here's the exact workflow:

### Phase A — Parallel Start (Now)

```
You (Backend)                          Collaborator (Frontend)
─────────────────                      ────────────────────────
git checkout -b feature/w1-1.3-master-erd    git checkout -b feature/w1-1.8-react-project-init
│                                             │
├─ Create all entities                        ├─ npx create-vite (TS)
├─ Flyway migrations                          ├─ Install Tailwind CSS
├─ PR → main                                  ├─ Setup project structure
│                                             ├─ Install Axios + React Router
git checkout -b feature/w1-1.6-user-entity    ├─ PR → main
│                                             │
├─ UserRepository                             (wait for backend auth PR)
├─ UserService
├─ UserDTO + CreateUserRequest
├─ PR → main

git checkout -b feature/w1-1.4-jwt-auth-backend
│
├─ JwtTokenProvider (polish existing)
├─ AuthController POST /api/v1/auth/login
├─ POST /api/v1/auth/register (sign up)
├─ BCrypt password hashing
├─ PR → main
```

### Phase B — After Backend Auth Merged

```
Collaborator (Frontend)
────────────────────────
git pull origin main
git checkout -b feature/w1-1.9-auth-guard-login-page
│
├─ AuthContext (React Context)
├─ AuthGuard component
├─ LoginPage (email + password)
├─ SignUpPage (register form)
├─ JWT storage (httpOnly or localStorage)
├─ PR → main
```

### 📌 Git Commands Cheat Sheet

```bash
# Starting a new feature
git checkout main
git pull origin main
git checkout -b feature/w1-1.4-jwt-auth-backend

# Working on your feature
git add .
git commit -m "[W1-1.4] Implement JwtTokenProvider with create/validate/parse"

# Ready for PR
git pull --rebase origin main
git push origin feature/w1-1.4-jwt-auth-backend
# → Open PR on GitHub
```

